                  </hi>. I am a baker, in Broad-street, Ratcliff. The prisoner was in my service—he collected money, and carried out bread—he has not paid me 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. from Mary Barton on the 18th of January, nor 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. from Louisa Bentley, nor 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from Elizabeth Payne—it was his duty to pay me when he received the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did not my fellow-servant agree to make this money up for me?<hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—you and he both absconded, and did not give me an opportunity of paying you your wages.</p>
